32/* Parse a BASEVER version string of the format "major.minor.patchlevel"
33 or "major.minor" to extract its components. */
34void
35parse_basever (int *major, int *minor, int *patchlevel)
36{
37 static int s_major = -1, s_minor, s_patchlevel;
38
39 if (s_major == -1)
40 if (sscanf (BASEVER, "%d.%d.%d", &s_major, &s_minor, &s_patchlevel) != 3)
41 {
42 sscanf (BASEVER, "%d.%d", &s_major, &s_minor);
43 s_patchlevel = 0;
44 }
45
46 if (major)
47 *major = s_major;
48
49 if (minor)
50 *minor = s_minor;
51
52 if (patchlevel)
53 *patchlevel = s_patchlevel;
54}
55
56
57/* Define __GNUC__, __GNUC_MINOR__, __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__ and __VERSION__. */
58static void
59define__GNUC__ (cpp_reader *pfile)
60{
61 int major, minor, patchlevel;
62
63 parse_basever (&major, &minor, &patchlevel);
64 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__GNUC__=%d", major);
65 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__GNUC_MINOR__=%d", minor);
66 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__=%d", patchlevel);
67 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__VERSION__=\"%s\"", version_string);
68 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_RELAXED=%d", MEMMODEL_RELAXED);
69 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_SEQ_CST=%d", MEMMODEL_SEQ_CST);
70 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_ACQUIRE=%d", MEMMODEL_ACQUIRE);
71 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_RELEASE=%d", MEMMODEL_RELEASE);
72 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_ACQ_REL=%d", MEMMODEL_ACQ_REL);
73 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__ATOMIC_CONSUME=%d", MEMMODEL_CONSUME);
74}

77/* Define various built-in CPP macros that depend on language-independent
78 compilation flags. */
79static void
80define_builtin_macros_for_compilation_flags (cpp_reader *pfile)
81{
82 if (flag_pic)
83 {
84 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__pic__=%d", flag_pic);
85 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__PIC__=%d", flag_pic);
86 }
87 if (flag_pie)
88 {
89 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__pie__=%d", flag_pie);
90 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__PIE__=%d", flag_pie);
91 }
92
93 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_ADDRESS)
94 cpp_define (pfile, "__SANITIZE_ADDRESS__");
95
96 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_THREAD)
97 cpp_define (pfile, "__SANITIZE_THREAD__");
98
99 if (optimize_size)
100 cpp_define (pfile, "__OPTIMIZE_SIZE__");
101 if (optimize)
102 cpp_define (pfile, "__OPTIMIZE__");
103
104 if (fast_math_flags_set_p (&global_options))
105 cpp_define (pfile, "__FAST_MATH__");
106 if (flag_signaling_nans)
107 cpp_define (pfile, "__SUPPORT_SNAN__");
108 if (!flag_errno_math)
109 cpp_define (pfile, "__NO_MATH_ERRNO__");
110
111 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__FINITE_MATH_ONLY__=%d",
112 flag_finite_math_only);
113 if (flag_cilkplus)
114 cpp_define (pfile, "__cilk=200");
115
116 if (flag_check_pointer_bounds)
117 cpp_define (pfile, "__CHKP__");
118}

120
121/* Define built-in macros for LP64 targets. */
122static void
123define_builtin_macros_for_lp64 (cpp_reader *pfile)
124{
125 if (TYPE_PRECISION (long_integer_type_node) == 64
126 && POINTER_SIZE == 64
127 && TYPE_PRECISION (integer_type_node) == 32)
128 {
129 cpp_define (pfile, "_LP64");
130 cpp_define (pfile, "__LP64__");
131 }
132}
133
134
135/* Define macros for size of basic C types. */
136static void
137define_builtin_macros_for_type_sizes (cpp_reader *pfile)
138{
139#define define_type_sizeof(NAME, TYPE) \
140 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, NAME"=" HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC, \
141 tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TYPE)))
142
143 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_INT__", integer_type_node);
144 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_LONG__", long_integer_type_node);
145 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_LONG_LONG__", long_long_integer_type_node);
146 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_SHORT__", short_integer_type_node);
147 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_FLOAT__", float_type_node);
148 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_DOUBLE__", double_type_node);
149 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_LONG_DOUBLE__", long_double_type_node);
150 define_type_sizeof ("__SIZEOF_SIZE_T__", size_type_node);
151
152#undef define_type_sizeof
153
154 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__CHAR_BIT__=%u",
155 TYPE_PRECISION (char_type_node));
156 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__BIGGEST_ALIGNMENT__=%d",
157 BIGGEST_ALIGNMENT / BITS_PER_UNIT);
158
159 /* Define constants useful for implementing endian.h. */
160 cpp_define (pfile, "__ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__=1234");
161 cpp_define (pfile, "__ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN__=4321");
162 cpp_define (pfile, "__ORDER_PDP_ENDIAN__=3412");
163
164 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN == BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
165 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__BYTE_ORDER__=%s",
166 (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN
167 ? "__ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN__"
168 : "__ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__"));
169 else
170 {
171 /* Assert that we're only dealing with the PDP11 case. */
172 gcc_assert (!BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN);
173 gcc_assert (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN);
174
175 cpp_define (pfile, "__BYTE_ORDER__=__ORDER_PDP_ENDIAN__");
176 }
177
178 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__FLOAT_WORD_ORDER__=%s",
179 (targetm.float_words_big_endian ()
180 ? "__ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN__"
181 : "__ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__"));
182
183 /* ptr_type_node can't be used here since ptr_mode is only set when
184 toplev calls backend_init which is not done with -E switch. */
185 cpp_define_formatted (pfile, "__SIZEOF_POINTER__=%d",
186 1 << ceil_log2 ((POINTER_SIZE + BITS_PER_UNIT - 1) / BITS_PER_UNIT));
187}
188
189
190/* Define macros builtins common to all language performing CPP
191 preprocessing. */
192void
193define_language_independent_builtin_macros (cpp_reader *pfile)
194{
195 define__GNUC__ (pfile);
196 define_builtin_macros_for_compilation_flags (pfile);
197 define_builtin_macros_for_lp64 (pfile);
198 define_builtin_macros_for_type_sizes (pfile);
199}
